abstract: After three months of demonstrations, the politicians and the protesters are talking past each other, there’s no prime minister and Iran maintains its influence.
snippet: After three months of demonstrations, the politicians and the protesters are talking past each other, there’s no prime minister and Iran maintains its influence.
lead_paragraph: BAGHDAD — For 12 weeks, Iraqi protesters have massed in the streets of Baghdad and cities in southern Iraq to demand the ouster of the government, an end to corruption and a halt to the overweening influence of Iran.

abstract: The draft law would punish judges who speak out on judicial independence. European officials say it continues the ruling party’s chipping away at Poland’s democracy.
snippet: The draft law would punish judges who speak out on judicial independence. European officials say it continues the ruling party’s chipping away at Poland’s democracy.
lead_paragraph: WARSAW — Poland’s right-wing governing party is pressing ahead with sweeping new legislation to tighten controls over judges, despite concerns from European Union officials that it would undermine the independence of the judiciary and the country’s democracy.

lead_paragraph: Mesut Özil is slowly disappearing from China. An online forum dedicated to him has closed. He has been scrubbed from the version of Pro Evolution Soccer, the video game, that is available in the country. Arsenal's last Premier League game, at home to Manchester City, was not broadcast on Chinese television. It is not clear, yet, how long the blackout will last.

abstract: President Donald Trump is in sunny Florida after his historic impeachment, while plans for his speedy trial back in Washington remained clouded. Senate leaders jockeying for leverage have failed to agree on procedures for the trial.
snippet: President Donald Trump is in sunny Florida after his historic impeachment, while plans for his speedy trial back in Washington remained clouded. Senate leaders jockeying for leverage have failed to agree on procedures for the trial.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Donald Trump is in sunny Florida after his historic impeachment, while plans for his speedy trial back in Washington remained clouded. Senate leaders jockeying for leverage have failed to agree on procedures for the trial.
headline_main: Plans for Impeachment Trial Get Foggy Before Holiday Break
headline_print_headline: Plans for Impeachment Trial Get Foggy Before Holiday Break

abstract: President Donald Trump complained Saturday about House Speaker Nancy Pelosi's delayed transmission of the articles of impeachment to the Senate, which may delay a trial in the GOP-controlled chamber.
snippet: President Donald Trump complained Saturday about House Speaker Nancy Pelosi's delayed transmission of the articles of impeachment to the Senate, which may delay a trial in the GOP-controlled chamber.
lead_paragraph: WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. — President Donald Trump complained Saturday about House Speaker Nancy Pelosi's delayed transmission of the articles of impeachment to the Senate, which may delay a trial in the GOP-controlled chamber.
headline_main: Trump Slams 'Unfair' Pelosi Delay, Rallies Conservatives
headline_print_headline: Trump Slams 'Unfair' Pelosi Delay, Rallies Conservatives

abstract: More than 1,500 protesters have been arrested across India in the past 10 days, officials said, as police try to quell  sometimes violent demonstrations against a citizenship law that critics say undermines the country's secular constitution.
snippet: More than 1,500 protesters have been arrested across India in the past 10 days, officials said, as police try to quell  sometimes violent demonstrations against a citizenship law that critics say undermines the country's secular constitution.
lead_paragraph: NEW DELHI/MUMBAI — More than 1,500 protesters have been arrested across India in the past 10 days, officials said, as police try to quell sometimes violent demonstrations against a citizenship law that critics say undermines the country's secular constitution.
headline_main: Hundreds Arrested in India During Days of Protests Over Citizenship Law
headline_print_headline: Hundreds Arrested in India During Days of Protests Over Citizenship Law

abstract: U.S. President Donald Trump signed a $1.4 trillion budget package for the fiscal year 2020 into law on Friday to avert a government shutdown, White House spokesman Judd Deere told journalists traveling with the president on Air Force One.
snippet: U.S. President Donald Trump signed a $1.4 trillion budget package for the fiscal year 2020 into law on Friday to avert a government shutdown, White House spokesman Judd Deere told journalists traveling with the president on Air Force One.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. President Donald Trump signed a $1.4 trillion budget package for the fiscal year 2020 into law on Friday to avert a government shutdown, White House spokesman Judd Deere told journalists traveling with the president on Air Force One.
headline_main: Trump Signs Spending Package to Avert Shutdown: White House Spokesman
headline_print_headline: Trump Signs Spending Package to Avert Shutdown: White House Spokesman

abstract: President Donald Trump signed off Friday on nearly $1.4 trillion in spending that will keep the government funded through Sept. 30, dodging the possibility of a shutdown ahead of what's expected to be a contentious election season.
snippet: President Donald Trump signed off Friday on nearly $1.4 trillion in spending that will keep the government funded through Sept. 30, dodging the possibility of a shutdown ahead of what's expected to be a contentious election season.
lead_paragraph: WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. — President Donald Trump signed off Friday on nearly $1.4 trillion in spending that will keep the government funded through Sept. 30, dodging the possibility of a shutdown ahead of what's expected to be a contentious election season.
headline_main: Trump Signs $1.4 Trillion in Spending, Avoids Shutdown
headline_print_headline: Trump Signs $1.4 Trillion in Spending, Avoids Shutdown
